Copec Buys Diego de Almagro Copper Project, Estrategia Reports

-- B y   J a m e s   A t t w o o d
-- 
2011-03-10T11:19:25Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-10/copec-buys-diego-de-almagro-copper-project-estrategia-reports.html
Empresas Copec SA, the holding
company controlled by Chile’s Angelini family, agreed to buy the
Diego de Almagro copper project for $40.1 million, Estrategia
reported.  Copec’s Cia Minera Can-Can unit will invest $227 million to
build the mine and processing plant, the Santiago-based
newspaper reported, citing a company statement.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Attwood at 
 jattwood3@bloomberg.net  